						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1420, Kālayukti, Jyēshṭha ba. 12, Saturday,</hi> corresponding to 1498 A.D., June 16.</p>						

						<p>It mentions the construction of a step-well and stone masonary by Kannama-Nāyuḍu, son of Gaṇṭṭa Yeṟṟama Nāyuḍu, for the merit of his parents and his elder brother Peda-Ammi Nāyuḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
